        {
            "body": "> I guess you're referring to this change here: scikit-image/scikit-image@645140c\r\n\r\nYes, moving from duplicating the loop and switching based on whether the step is 1, to an approach based on while loops. I dislike both approaches :)\r\n\r\n> So it needs to generate code that determines the step at runtime and allows the loop to run in both directions,\r\n\r\nRight. That makes sense. Thanks for the explanation.\r\n\r\nWould it be possible to somehow annotate the step as being `>0`? Or to mark the `range` as increasing/decreasing?",
